library.description:
With Jailed you can:


execute an untrusted code in a sandboxed environment of a worker (in a browser) or a restricted subprocess (Node.js);
export a set of functions into a sandbox and backwards (thus defining a precise permissions);
run untrusted code from a string or from a file;
isomorphic syntax works unchanged both in browser and in Node.js;
control the execution launching and shutting down the code anytime;
